snippet.authorDisplayName: The Man, The Myth, The Legend
snippet.textDisplay: I am a cancer survivor, and I can tell you that chemotherapy changes everything about you and takes ALL of your energy. I was also terminal at one point, but I lived through it. I had a mediport installed and I was being injected with 4 types of chemotherapy at one time, 6 days a week. I would also drive myself to and from the hospital an hour each way in Tampa, Florida traffic. The chemo made me SO sick. I was obviously also bald. I lost 93 lbs in 30 days...seriously. However much the experience sucked, it saved my life. Miracles happen every day. I give Jackson ALOT of credit because he's very upbeat and positive given his condition. It was very cool of you all to bring him on the show and make his dream come true.
snippet.textOriginal: I am a cancer survivor, and I can tell you that chemotherapy changes everything about you and takes ALL of your energy. I was also terminal at one point, but I lived through it.
